BRIEFLY: CONSUMER NEWS 
GM Recalling 656,000 Cars: About 616,000 1988- to 1990-model Pontiac Grand 
Prixes, Oldsmobile Cutlass Supremes, Buick Regal coupes and Chevrolet Lumina 
coupes are being recalled to strengthen a guide loop in the shoulder belt 
system that could fail to restrain occupants during an accident. About 40,000 
Chevrolet Camaros and Pontiac Firebirds are being recalled to correct possible 
fuel leaks. General Motors will make repairs free. 
